<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-09-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-09-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="61" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d61">
                    <head>No. 61.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Logan</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-09-14"><hi rend="italic">September</hi> 14,
                            1883</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 67.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your No. 113, communicating the
                        text of the protocol signed between General Iglesias and the Chilian, Señor
                        Novoa, leading to a definitive treaty of peace, I inclose for your
                        information a copy of an instruction (No. 8) to Mr. Phelps, our minister at
                        Lima, on the subject.<note n="*" xml:id="d61fn1">See Mr. Frelinghuysen to
                            Mr. Phelps, No. 8, August 25, 1883, <hi rend="italic">post.</hi></note></p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>